9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
10 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
11 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
12 The State Regents for Higher Education may approve functional
13 exceptions. "Functional exception" means an expansion or exception
14 to assigned institutional function or mission to permit an
15 institution of higher education within The State System of Higher
16 Education to offer courses or degree programs outside the
17 institution's assigned function or mission to meet unmet workforce
18 needs.
